				\begin{document}
$$\displaystyle \begin{aligned} (\alpha | \beta | \gamma). \end{aligned} $$
\end{document}

The γ field describes the objective function. objective function In this book, we consider the following possible values of this field: 
An entry of Lmax means that the maximum lateness is to be minimized.
Maximum latenessmaximum lateness is defined as the difference between the completion time and the deadline, maximized over all jobs.
Maximum lateness is negative if all tasks complete before their deadline.
An entry of MSmax denotes the case of minimizing the makespan (the time at which the last job finishes).
The makespanmakespan is defined as36.3MSmax=maxi(fi)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
