schedulingrate monotonic ˜ Rate monotonic (RM) scheduling [348] is probably the most well-known scheduling algorithm for independent periodic tasks. Rate monotonic scheduling is based on the following assumptions (“RM assumptions”): 
All tasks that have hard deadlines are periodic.deadline
All tasks are independent.
Di = Ti, for all tasks.
Ci is constant and is known for all tasks. Self-suspension (voluntarily relinquishing the execution) is not allowed.
The time required for context switching is negligible.
For a single processor and for n tasks, the accumulated utilization Usum does not exceed the following bound: 6.7Usum=∑i=1nCiTi≤n(21∕n−1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
