$$\tau _{i+1}^{\prime }$$
\end{document}, containing the execution times of the two original tasks. This folding is feasible if the total execution time of the two tasks does not exceed the period of τi+1. The process can be repeated in the same way with the next lower-priority task. Overall, folding is feasible as long as the overall utilization does not exceed 1. □Fig. 6.16
Folding of tasks of adjacent priorities

