$$\displaystyle \begin{aligned} \begin{array}{rcl} DBF(\tau_i,t) & =&\displaystyle \max \left(0,\left(\left\lfloor \frac{t-D_i}{T_i}\right\rfloor +1 \right) * C_i \right ) {} \end{array} \end{aligned} $$
\end{document} Density and the demand bound function are related:

For all tasks τiand for all t ≥ 0: 6.14t∗densi≥DBF(τi,t)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
